# Proposed Update — academic-plotting.md

**Source:** SkillTest R1.A (3 cases) + R1.B (3 cases) + visual review by user.
**Status:** Draft only. Do not apply to
`/Users/mjm/MinionsOS/minions/roles/writer/skills/academic-plotting.md` until
the user explicitly approves the R1 synthesis port plan.

## What to add

The current `academic-plotting.md` covers venue-standard styling, colourblind-
safe palette, vector + raster outputs. Add the following hard rules at the
top of the Procedure section.

### Add Rule: rcParams discipline (FIRST move in any plotting script)

Every plotting script for a paper figure must lead with:

```python
import matplotlib as mpl
mpl.rcParams.update({
    "font.family": "sans-serif",
    "font.sans-serif": ["Arial", "Helvetica", "DejaVu Sans", "Liberation Sans"],
    "svg.fonttype": "none",     # editable text in SVG (NOT rasterised paths)
    "pdf.fonttype": 42,         # editable TrueType in PDF
    "axes.spines.right": False,
    "axes.spines.top": False,
    "axes.linewidth": 0.8,
    "legend.frameon": False,
})
```

Why: SkillTest R1.A and R1.B baselines (no skill loaded) emitted SVGs with
0 `<text>` nodes — text was rasterised to path geometry, which is
not editable by venue copy-editors. Both candidates emitted 18 to 62
`<text>` nodes with explicit `font-family`. This is a HARD submission
requirement for Nature-family vector artwork.

### Add Rule: PALETTE-dict pattern

Define a single PALETTE dict at the top of any multi-panel plot script;
thread it through every panel:

```python
PALETTE = {
    "signal": "#0F4D92",       # the intervention / treatment / KO direction
    "signal_soft": "#B4C0E4",  # subordinate signal
    "neutral": "#767676",      # control / WT / non-direction
    "neutral_light": "#D8D8D8",
    "accent": "#E4CCD8",       # secondary discriminator
    "accent_dark": "#9A4D8E",
    "black": "#272727",
}
```

With the constraint:

> **Reserve green and red for directional signals only** (gain / loss / up /
> down). Use neutrals (grey, single-blue family, faint pink, faint purple)
> for non-directional categorical labels. Do NOT use a saturated 3-or-4
> hue cycle for a cluster sidebar or category labels — it burns the
> green/red pair on labels that don't carry direction.

Why: SkillTest R1.A case-heatmap baseline used a saturated `#4C72B0 /
#55A868 / #C44E52` cluster bar that fought the RdBu_r diverging body.
Both candidates used neutral / signal-blue / faint-pink and the user
approved.

### Add Rule: Default figsize in inches, NOT mm

Default sizes:
- single panel: `figsize=(6, 4)` inches
- 2-panel side-by-side: `figsize=(10, 4)`
- 4-panel hero: `figsize=(11, 6)` (see [[figure-layout-defaults]])

Compress to exact mm only at submission packaging stage, AFTER the layout
has been visually confirmed in PNG preview. Do NOT lead with
`figsize=(width_mm/25.4, height_mm/25.4)` — that produced unreadable
cramming in SkillTest R1.A case-bar.

### Add Rule: TwoSlopeNorm for diverging colormaps

For any heatmap that uses a diverging colormap (RdBu_r, BrBG, PiYG, etc),
explicitly centre the norm at zero:

```python
import matplotlib as mpl
norm = mpl.colors.TwoSlopeNorm(vmin=-vmax, vcenter=0, vmax=vmax)
im = ax.imshow(data, cmap="RdBu_r", norm=norm)
```

Do NOT rely on `vmin/vmax` symmetry by data luck — the zero line on a
z-score or log-fold-change heatmap is load-bearing.

### Add Rule: Outside tick discipline

```python
ax.tick_params(direction="out", length=2.2, width=0.6)
```

Inside ticks fight the data; outside ticks read as instrument-style
chrome and stay out of the way.

## What to leave unchanged

- The colourblind-safe palette intent.
- The vector + raster outputs requirement.
- The diagram-vs-numerical-axes split.

## What NOT to add (handled by sibling skill)

Multi-panel layout (4-panel hero default, no empty quadrants, no over-
stretched panels, layout-budget triage) belongs in
[[figure-layout-defaults]], not here. `academic-plotting.md` covers
content discipline (palette, fonts, ticks, vector output); the layout
discipline lives separately.

## Why these are the right additions

Five additions justified by R1 cross-skill evidence:

| Rule | R1.A nature-figure evidence | R1.B scientific-figure-making evidence |
|---|---|---|
| rcParams editable text | All 3 cases: 0→18-60 `<text>` | All 3 cases: 0→18-62 `<text>` |
| PALETTE-dict | case-multi-panel +2 dim | case-multi-panel +2 dim (palette user-approved) |
| figsize in inches | case-bar fail (mm cramming) | case-bar OK (lighter rule set) |
| TwoSlopeNorm | case-heatmap +1 dim | case-heatmap +1 dim |
| Outside ticks | All 3 cases | All 3 cases |

Every rule has evidence from at least 2 cases (across the two skills).
None is a one-shot.
